Course Info: Describe how biology as a field interfaces with other fields, in particular the arts, business and psychology. Explain how we use evidence to make decisions and why this is important to consider when promoting science literacy. Course Info Translate: Biology intersects with other fields such as the arts, business, and psychology. We use evidence to make decisions, which is crucial for promoting science literacy. Course Title: Rastreo de los contactos de la COVID-19
Course Info: Describir la evolución natural del SARS-CoV-2, incluyendo el período de contagio, el cuadro clínico de la COVID-19 y las pruebas de cómo se contagia.Definir un contacto infeccioso y el tiempo de la intervención de salud pública a través del rastreo de contactos.Mostrar la utilidad de la investigación de casos y del rastreo de contactos, identificar los obstáculos frecuentes y las estrategias para superarlos.Presentar algunas consideraciones éticas acerca del rastreo de contactos, el aislamiento y la cuarentena. Not specified Aspectos básicos de la COVID-19, Aspectos básicos del rastreo de los contactos de la COVID-19, Pasos para investigar casos y rastrear sus contactos, Ética del rastreo de los contactos y herramientas tecnológicas, Habilidades para lograr una comunicación eficaz, Evaluación final (se califica) Health
Course Info Translate: Describe the natural evolution of SARS-CoV-2, including the period of contagion, the clinical picture of COVID-19, and evidence of how it is transmitted. Define an infectious contact and the time for public health intervention through contact tracing. Show the usefulness of case investigation and contact tracing, identify common obstacles and strategies to overcome them. Present some ethical considerations about contact tracing, isolation, and quarantine. Basic aspects of COVID-19, Basic aspects of contact tracing for COVID-19, Steps to investigate cases and trace their contacts, Ethics of contact tracing and technological tools, Skills to achieve effective communication, Final evaluation (graded) Health.

Provide reliable supervision and stabilization to patients in severe respiratory distress, including early use of a ventilator, intubation, oxygen, personal protective equipment. Module 1: Main characteristics of COVID-19 and PPE, MODULE 2: Clinical assessment of COVID-19 patients, MODULE 3: Diagnostic assessment of COVID-19 patients, MODULE 4: Early Treatment of Dyspneic COVID-19 Patient, MODULE 5: Advanced Treatment of Severely Dyspneic COVID-19 Patient, MODULE 6: Initial Management of the Ventilator and Troubleshooting in COVID-19 Patients.

Course Title: Core 2: OS, Software, Security and Operational Procedures
Course Info: List common features and commands of Microsoft Windows, Apple macOS, Linux OSs, and adjust preferences with command line and console tools. Describe OS features, how to install and update OS, troubleshoot common issues, and summarize the importance of SOHO networks. Explain the advantages of using active directory, MS Windows security tools, and data destruction to secure mobile devices. Evaluate IT support practices while assessing the utility of privacy, automation, safety, and control methods and define malware best practices. Technical Support, security, Operating Systems, IT Troubleshooting, Mobile Devices Microsoft Windows Operating System Overview and Management, macOS, Linux, and Mobile Operating System Overview and Management, Device and Home Network Security, Software Troubleshooting, Operational Procedures, Final Exam\xa0and Honors Final Project Information Technology
Course Info Translate:
In this course, you will learn about the common features and commands of Microsoft Windows, Apple macOS, and Linux operating systems. You will also learn how to adjust preferences using command line and console tools. The course will cover OS features, installation and updating procedures, troubleshooting common issues, and the importance of small office/home office (SOHO) networks.

Additionally, you will explore the advantages of using active directory, Microsoft Windows security tools, and data destruction techniques to secure mobile devices. You will evaluate IT support practices, considering the utility of privacy, automation, safety, and control methods, as well as defining best practices for dealing with malware.

Topics covered include technical support, security, operating systems, IT troubleshooting, mobile devices, device and home network security, software troubleshooting, operational procedures, and preparation for the final exam and honors final project in Information Technology.
Course Title Translate: Core 2: OS, Software, Security and Operational Procedures

Course Title: Explore Core Data Concepts in Microsoft Azure
Course Info: Describe core data concepts. Identify how data is defined and stored.Describe data job roles. Describe and differentiate batch and streaming data. Identify characteristics of relational and non-relational data. Microsoft Azure, Data Storage, Data Concepts, Data Management Core Data Concepts and Roles, Concepts of Relational and Non-relational Data Information Technology
Course Info Translate:
Core data concepts refer to the fundamental principles and elements related to data. This includes how data is defined and stored, as well as the various job roles involved in managing data. 

Data can be stored and processed in two main ways: batch processing, where data is collected and processed in large chunks at scheduled intervals, and streaming data, where data is processed in real-time as it is generated.

Relational data refers to data that is structured in tables with defined relationships between them, while non-relational data does not adhere to a strict tabular structure and can be more flexible in terms of data storage.

In the context of Microsoft Azure and data management, understanding core data concepts and roles is essential for effectively storing, managing, and analyzing data.
Course Title Translate: Explore Core Data Concepts in Microsoft Azure

Course Info: Describe the characteristics of relational data Describe types of non-relational and NoSQL databasesDefine types of non-relational dataChoose the most suitable Explore relational data workload offerings  Microsoft Azure, Database (DBMS), SQL, Data Management, NoSQL Relational Data Services in Microsoft Azure, Explore Provisioning, Deploying, and Querying Relational Data in Microsoft Azure Information Technology
Course Info Translate:
The characteristics of relational data include structured data organized in tables with defined relationships between them. Non-relational databases, also known as NoSQL databases, come in various types such as document-oriented, key-value, column-family, and graph databases. Non-relational data is typically unstructured or semi-structured data that does not fit well into traditional relational databases.

In Microsoft Azure, there are relational data workload offerings such as Database Management Systems (DBMS), SQL, and NoSQL Relational Data Services. These services allow for provisioning, deploying, and querying relational data in Azure's Information Technology environment.

Course Title: Cloud Computing Primer: Software as a Service (SaaS)
Course Info: Describe at least three advantages and disadvantages of cloud computingProvide a strategy on how an ISV can utilize SaaS to promote their growthExplore the application of a SaaS cloud computing model through a demo engagement Cloud Applications, Software As A Service (SAAS), Cloud Computing Cloud Computing Primer, SaaS Considerations & Expansion, SaaS Applications & Adoption, SaaS Demo Information Technology
Course Info Translate:
Advantages of cloud computing include cost savings, scalability, and flexibility. Disadvantages include security concerns, dependency on internet connectivity, and potential downtime.

An ISV can utilize SaaS to promote their growth by offering subscription-based services, reaching a wider audience, and providing regular updates and improvements to their software.

To explore the application of a SaaS cloud computing model through a demo engagement, the ISV can showcase the benefits of their software through a trial version, provide training and support to potential customers, and gather feedback for further enhancements.
Course Title Translate: Cloud Computing Primer: Software as a Service (SaaS)

Course Info: Describe the fundamental processes involved in reading.Explain the natural acquisition of literacy and its implications for society.Identify possible technological advances in literacy. Not specified Week 1 Introduction, Challenges, and Language, Week 2 Acquiring Spoken and Written Language, Week 3 Reading, Early Reading, and Technological Innovations Information Technology
Course Info Translate:
The fundamental processes involved in reading include recognizing letters and words, understanding their meanings, and making connections between them to comprehend the text. The natural acquisition of literacy refers to the process by which individuals learn to read and write through exposure to language in their environment. This has significant implications for society as literacy is essential for communication, education, and participation in the workforce.

Possible technological advances in literacy include the use of digital tools and resources to enhance reading skills, such as e-books, audiobooks, and interactive learning platforms. In the specified weeks of the course, topics will cover Introduction, Challenges, and Language in Week 1, Acquiring Spoken and Written Language in Week 2, and Reading, Early Reading, and Technological Innovations in Information Technology in Week 3.

Course Info Translate: This text discusses the career development and progression of a Cybersecurity professional from entry-level to Chief Information Security Officer (CISO). It defines and describes the role and responsibilities of a CISO in planning for cybersecurity, as well as the development of a cybersecurity governance program and the involvement of the CISO in it. The text also discusses the strategic responsibilities of the CISO in overseeing an organization's cybersecurity program, including risk management, contingency planning, cybersecurity staffing, cybersecurity governance, and compliance with cybersecurity regulations. It also introduces the Culminating Project (Capstone Course) and various case project assignments related to Information Technology.
Course Title Translate: Road to the CISO – Culminating Project Course

Azure Kubernetes Service, Network security group, Web application firewall, Front Door and Application Gateway, Azure Firewall Perimeter Security, Network security, Host and container security, Project and graded assessment Information Technology
Course Info Translate: Defense in depth is a security strategy that involves implementing multiple layers of security controls to protect against different types of threats. This includes core security concepts such as network security, host and container security, and perimeter security. In order to implement defense in depth in Azure, you can configure an Azure Application Gateway to protect your perimeter, as well as deploy the Azure Web Application Firewall. Other tools that can be used for defense in depth in Azure include Azure Kubernetes Service, Network Security Group, Azure Firewall, Front Door, and Application Gateway. It is important to regularly review and assess the security measures in place to ensure they are effective in protecting your IT infrastructure.
